 132 as references to the birth of spirit offspring by exalted married couples in the celestial kingdom</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Mormon+History&amp;rft.atitle=%27A+Continuation+of+the+Seeds%27%3A+Joseph+Smith+and+Spirit+Birth&amp;rft.ssn=fall&amp;rft.volume=38&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=105-130&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A254493140%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F23292634%23id-name%3DJSTOR&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F23292634&amp;rft.aulast=Hales&amp;rft.aufirst=Brian&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F23292634&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AExaltation+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Godhood-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Godhood_2-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFCarter1992" class="citation book cs1">Carter, K. Codell (1992). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/digital/collection/EoM/id/3734">"Godhood"</a>. In Ludlow, Daniel H. (ed.). <i><a href="/wiki/Encyclopedia_of_Mormonism" title="Encyclopedia of Mormonism">Encyclopedia of Mormonism</a></i>. New York City: <a href="/wiki/Macmillan_Publishers" title="Macmillan Publishers">Macmillan Publishers</a>. pp.&#160;553, 555. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-02-904040-9" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-02-904040-9"><bdi>978-0-02-904040-9</bdi></a>. <q>They [resurrected and perfected mortals] will dwell again with God the Father, and live and act like him in endless worlds of happiness ... above all they will have the power of procreating endless lives. ... Those who become like him will likewise contribute to this eternal process by adding further spirit offspring to the eternal family.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=Godhood&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.place=New+York+City&amp;rft.pages=553%2C+555&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan+Publishers&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-02-904040-9&amp;rft.aulast=Carter&amp;rft.aufirst=K.+Codell&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fdigital%2Fcollection%2FEoM%2Fid%2F3734&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AExaltation+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Fundamentals-3"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Fundamentals_3-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Fundamentals_3-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/bc/content/shared/content/english/pdf/language-materials/31129_eng.pdf#page=210"><i>Gospel Fundamentals</i></a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span> (2002&#160;ed.). Salt Lake City: <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. p.&#160;201. <q>They [the people who will live in the celestial kingdom] will receive everything our Father in Heaven has and will become like Him. They will even be able to have spirit children and make new worlds for them to live on, and do all the things our Father in Heaven has done.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Gospel+Fundamentals&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City&amp;rft.pages=201&amp;rft.edition=2002&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fbc%2Fcontent%2Fshared%2Fcontent%2Fenglish%2Fpdf%2Flanguage-materials%2F31129_eng.pdf%23page%3D210&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AExaltation+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
