<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrooke1996" class="citation book cs1">Brooke, John L. (May 31, 1996). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=eyvftt-1F_kC&amp;pg=PA294"><i>The Refiner's Fire: The Making of Mormon Cosmology, 1644-1844</i></a>. Cambridge, UK: <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>. p.&#160;294. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0521565646" title="Special:BookSources/978-0521565646"><bdi>978-0521565646</bdi></a>. <q>The frequency of second anointings declined after the turn of the century, and they were virtually eliminated under the authority of Heber J. Grant in the 1920s, to the point that modern Mormons are generally unaware of the rituals existence ....</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Refiner%27s+Fire%3A+The+Making+of+Mormon+Cosmology%2C+1644-1844&amp;rft.place=Cambridge%2C+UK&amp;rft.pages=294&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=1996-05-31&amp;rft.isbn=978-0521565646&amp;rft.aulast=Brooke&amp;rft.aufirst=John+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3Deyvftt-1F_kC%26pg%3DPA294&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AExaltation+%28Mormonism%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
